text: James Skinner (by 1489 – 30 July 1558), of Reigate, Surrey, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Reigate in 1542 and November 1554. ==References== Category:15th-century births Category:1558 deaths Category:People from Surrey Category:English MPs 1542–1544 Category:English MPs 1554–1555
